<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step01_FreezingUiProblem"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 1 - The Freezing UI Problem">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step01ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 1: The Freezing UI Problem"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">THE PROBLEM: When you do long work on the UI thread, the whole window FREEZES.

In a WPF app, there is ONE special thread called the "UI thread" (or "main thread").
This thread is responsible for drawing buttons, handling clicks, updating text, etc.

If you run a slow operation (like downloading a file, reading a database, or even
just Thread.Sleep) directly on this UI thread, the window cannot redraw or respond
to clicks until that slow operation finishes. The app appears "frozen" or "hung".

Click the button below to simulate a 3-second blocking operation.
Try to move the window or click anything while it is running - you cannot!</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}" 
                    Content="Run BLOCKING operation (will freeze UI for 3 seconds)"
                    Command="{Binding RunBlockingCommand}"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" Margin="0,15,0,5"
                       Text="The counter below updates every second to prove the UI is alive. Watch it STOP when you click the blocking button:"/>

            <TextBlock FontSize="24" FontWeight="Bold" 
                       Foreground="#E63946" Margin="0,5,0,10" 
                       Text="{Binding Counter, StringFormat='Counter: {0}'}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="200"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
